725834f-a.text:
123rd Street, adjoining and at the S.E. corner of 22nd Avenue, viewing north toward the latter and showing some old homes and St. Johns Evangelical Lutheran Church. The church is at the corner. The dwellings (right to left) were owned, in 1873, by C. Piereth, P. Ulck, and J. Harrold. The church, too, was standing in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932

725835f-a.text:
123rd Street (left), at the N.E. corner of 22nd Avenue. The house was owned by F. Conlon in 1873.
March 16,1932
F.L. Sperr
